{
  "texts": [
    "Despite using the optimal configuration for each chunker (minimizing errors), Breakpoint-based Chunker still produced chunks containing only a single sentence, such as Chunk 3 and 5.",
    "Additionally, separating Sentences 5 and 6, which both discussed \"Interact Electronics Inc,\" was an especially poor decision.",
    "These examples underscore that semantic similarity alone is not a reliable measure for effective chunking, and it may be less useful than straightforward positional information.",
    "Retrieval and Answer Generation",
    "In addition to dunzhang/stella_en_1.5B_v5, we experimented on 2 other embedding models on the MTEB benchmark: BAAI/bge-large-en-v1.5 and all-mpnet-base-v2."
  ]
}